    • Method Detail

      • get

        public GetResult<byte[]> get(long timestamp,
                             java.lang.String key)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalDataMatrix
        Returns the value for the given key at the given timestamp together with the time range in which it is valid.
        Parameters:
        timestamp - The timestamp at which to get the value for the given key. Must not be negative.
        key - The key to get the value for. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        A ranged result. The result object itself is guaranteed to be non-null. Contains the value for the given key at the given timestamp, or contains a null-value if the key does not exist in this matrix at the given timestamp. The range of the returned object represents the period in which the given key is bound to the returned value.

        Parameters:
        time - The timestamp at which to add the given contents to this matrix. Must not be negative.
        contents - The key-value pairs to add, as a map. Must not be null. If the map is empty, this method is a no-op and returns immediately.

      • history

        public java.util.Iterator<java.lang.Long> history(long maxTime,
                                                  java.lang.String key)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalDataMatrix
        Returns the history of the given key, i.e. all timestamps at which the given key changed its value due to a commit.
        Parameters:
        maxTime - The maximum timestamp to consider. Only timestamps equal to or lower than this value will be considered. Must not be negative.
        key - The key to get the commit timestamps for. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        An iterator over all commit timestamps on the given key, up to the given maximum timestamp. May be empty, but never null.

        Description copied from interface: TemporalDataMatrix
        Returns an iterator over all entries in this matrix.
        Parameters:

      • lastCommitTimestamp

        public long lastCommitTimestamp(java.lang.String key)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalDataMatrix
        Returns the timestamp at which the last (latest) commit has happened on the given key.
        Parameters:
        key - The key in question. Must not be null.
        Returns:
        The latest commit timestamp, or a negative value if there has never been a commit to this key in this matrix.

      • rollback

        public void rollback(long timestamp)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalDataMatrix
        Performs a rollback of the contents of this matrix to the given timestamp.

        Any entries which have been inserted after the given timestamp will be removed during the process.

        Parameters:
        timestamp - The timestamp to roll back to. Must not be negative.

      • getModificationsBetween

        public java.util.Iterator<TemporalKey> getModificationsBetween(long timestampLowerBound,
                                                               long timestampUpperBound)
        Description copied from interface: TemporalDataMatrix
        Returns the temporal keys that were modified in the given time range.
        Parameters:
        timestampLowerBound - The lower bound on the timestamp to search for (inclusive). Must not be negative. Must be less than or equal to the upper bound.
        timestampUpperBound - The upper bound on the timestamp to search for (inclusive). Must not be negative. Must be larger than or equal to the lower bound.
        Returns:
        An iterator over the temporal keys that were modified in the given time range. May be empty, but never null.
